I"ˆ<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/rich-mental-model-repository-is-conductive-of-insight">Mental models</a> can be seen as constellations in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/concept-learning-is-few-shot-scaffolding-supported-by-working-memory">conceptual space</a>, systematic patterns of interrelatedness supported by strong <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/metaphor-is-central-to-cognition">metaphors</a>. This analogy plays extremely nicely with the view of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/conceptual-gateways-are-like-wormholes">conceptual gateways as wormholes</a>, in that <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/rich-mental-model-repository-is-conductive-of-insight">mental models</a> are the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/explicit-position-cues-describe-conceptual-structure">conceptual structures</a> which can be transferred.</p>
